7. SMOKE TEST #8 — PARTIAL SUCCESS (spot termination)
================================================================================

  Project: smoke-20260426-224020
  Started: 22:40:23 UTC

  Pre-flight: all passed (spot-queue ENABLED, 2 CEs VALID, S3 accessible)

  Pipeline progress:
    AWS_DOWNLOAD     2/2  completed
    FASTERQ_DUMP     2/2  completed
    count_reads      2/2  completed
    clean_reads      2/2  completed
    get_software_versions  1/1  completed
    profile_taxa     0/2  running when aborted
    profile_function 0/2  running when aborted

  Failure: profile_function (SRR6664342) — "Host EC2 (instance
  i-018922efc40d62510) terminated." This is a spot instance reclamation,
  NOT a database or AMI issue.

  Instance details:
    Type: m8g.4xlarge (Batch chose this from the allowed instance types)
    AMI:  ami-0b87926a60df7043e (custom AMI — correct!)
    Launch: 22:41:49 UTC
    Terminated: 22:51:18 UTC (Service initiated — spot reclamation)
    Worker active time: ~10 min

  Key validation: worker booted and started processing in ~1 minute
  (vs 20+ minutes with S3 sync). No "ChocoPhlAn database does not exist"
  error. HUMAnN was actively running for ~6 minutes before spot reclamation.

  The custom AMI eliminated the boot-time sync problem. The spot termination
  is normal operational risk — production runs use `-resume` to recover.

